title: Echoes of Moonlight (Remastered)
author: AvaTar ArTs
lyrics:
[Verse]
In moonlit alleys we used to sing
Now I roam these streets alone
Beneath the stars my heart it stings
Darkened nights I've always known
[Verse 2]
Love was sweet but now it's gone
Echoes of a distant tune
Howling cat took my song
Left me with this heavy gloom
[Chorus]
No more love songs in the night
Only echoes of our fight
Broken dreams they scatter wide
In this alley where I hide
[Verse 3]
I tried to win your heart in vain
Sung my soul beneath the moon
But your love was just a chain
Now I howl a different tune
[Bridge]
No more kisses in the rain
No more songs without the pain
Freedom found in broken chains
Raccoon heartbeats gone insane
[Chorus]
No more love songs in the night
Only echoes of our fight
Broken dreams they scatter wide
In this alley where I hide

title: Sammy's Serenade (Remastered)2
author: AvaTar ArTs
lyrics:
Sammy sang in moonlit nights

With raccoon band and alley lights
Love ballads soft in the dark
Till one night love left a mark
[Verse 2]
Howling cat took Sammy's throne
Winning contest all alone
Sammy's heart was torn in twos
Music now laced with blues
[Chorus]
Oh Sammy why oh why
Did the alley cat steal your sky
Once you sang of love and light
Now your songs bite in the night
[Verse 3]
Raccoon band plays out of tune
Since that fateful night in June
Howling cat's song took the crowd
Left poor Sammy crying loud
[Verse 4]
Sammy’s tunes have lost their glee
Heartbreak under the willow tree

Ballads now with teeth and claws
Raccoons play with hidden flaws

[Bridge]
Moonlit alleys still remember
Songs of love in soft September
Sammy sings with feral spite
Turning love into a fight

title: Kings and Queens of Litter (Remastered)
author: AvaTar ArTs
lyrics:
[Verse]
In the shadows where the alley cats prowl
Broken dreams and shattered glass
East of town
We scavenge treasure from the tale of the city’s frown
Live fast
Live trash
Beneath the moon’s hostile howl

[Verse 2]
By the fire's orange glow
Our kingdom rises from the scrap
She hums the blues of a life caught in the traps
Rusty hearts beating in sync
Wrapped in plastic wrap
We're royalty of refuse
Love in a discarded map

[Chorus]
Love is rubbish
Let's get trashy in the moonlight
Kings and queens of litter
In the city's blight
With dumpsters for a throne
And cans filled with delight
We find love burning bright by the polluted light

[Verse 3]
Her eyes are diamonds among the broken bottles
We drink cheap wine from a paper bag throttle
Stories of old stardust
Told in street lamp wattles
With every beat from the drum of an empty milk bottle

[Verse 4]
The stray dogs bark a mournful tune
Alley's symphony
Our romance is feral
Wild as the wind
Unchained
Free
No fancy words
Nor clean papers decree
In the trash we thrive
Hearts wild and debris

[Chorus]
Love is rubbish
Let's get trashy in the moonlight
Kings and queens of litter
In the city's blight
With dumpsters for a throne
And cans filled with delight
We find love burning bright by the polluted light

title: Junkyard Symphony Scraps2 (Remastered)
author: AvaTar ArTs
lyrics:
[Verse]
In the junkyard where I played
With the scraps and broken dreams
Found a world where music stayed
In the quiet metal seams

[Verse 2]
Old cans would be my drums
Broken strings would be my tune
For every beat my heart thums
In the light of the junkyard moon

[Chorus]
Play my junkyard symphony
Hear the magic in the night
Raise our hands in unity
Feel the hope and see the light

[Verse 3]
When the shadows start to creep
And the world begins to fade
From the silence deep deep deep
Music always finds its way

[Bridge]
With a song we fight the dark
Raise our voice in harmony
Every note will make its mark
In our junkyard symphony

[Chorus]
Play my junkyard symphony
Hear the magic in the night
Raise our hands in unity
Feel the hope and see the light

title: Recycled Symphony2.1 (Remastered)
author: AvaTar ArTs
lyrics:
[Verse]
Broken bottles make a sound
Cans and lids we gathered 'round
Junkyard piles turned to gold
He showed a story to be told

[Verse 2]
Strings from wires strummed with care
Keys from pipes everywhere
He found rhythm in the waste
Gave each piece a special place

[Chorus]
Recycled symphony
Playing for you and me
Turn the trash to timeless truth
Music from the old to new

[Verse 3]
Hearts and hands came to play
Instruments of every kind
Together we made music strong
Finding beauty in the wrong

[Bridge]
With every beat we take a stand
Inspire hope across this land
From the wreckage we arise
With harmony we touch the skies

[Chorus]
Recycled symphony
Playing for you and me
Turn the trash to timeless truth
Music from the old to new

title: The Alley King (Remastered)
author: AvaTar ArTs
lyrics:
[Verse]
Once the king of this place called the alley
Sammy ruled with his tune and his rally
But a howling cat came and stole his throne
Now Sammy sings his blues all alone

[Verse 2]
In the moonlight he strums with sadness
Echoes bounce off the walls of his madness
Every note from his heart always true
In the shadows he fights with the blue

[Chorus]
Oh Sammy once the alley king
Now his chords just cry and sting
With every whisper of his string
He dreams of the days he used to sing

[Verse 3]
On the corner where the streetlight flickers
He remembers when his fame was thicker
But the howling cat's got a brand new show
And now Sammy's sorrow starts to flow

[Bridge]
Heartbreak's the beat that he now knows
Defiance burns where his music grows
He won't give up these alleyways
'Cause in his soul the fire stays

[Chorus]
Oh Sammy once the alley king
Now his chords just cry and sting
With every whisper of his string
He dreams of the days he used to sing

title: Heartbreak hope and memories-v4-2-1
author: AvaTar ArTs
lyrics:
[Verse]
Moonlit valleys calling
Willow trees sway slow
Heartbreak like a whisper
In the still of night it grows

[Verse 2]
Once was joy in morning
Now the shadows cast so deep
Echoes of the laughter
Fade into the dreams we keep

[Chorus]
Heartbreak hope and memories
Dancing with the trees
Moonlit nights and willow whispers
Take me back please

[Verse 3]
In the night so silent
Loneliness does creep
Yet the moon she guides me
Through the pain in which I weep

[Chorus]
Heartbreak hope and memories
Dancing with the trees
Moonlit nights and willow whispers
Take me back please

[Bridge]
From the sorrow rises
Hope that never dies
Whispering willows listen
To the heartfelt cries

title: Love in Imperfection (Remastered)2
author: AvaTar ArTs
lyrics:
[Verse]
Rusty chains
Tangled 'round a broken swing
A dandelion blooms where the thorns cling
Scratched up records play the same sad song
We danced in shadows
Where we both belong

[Verse 2]
Graffiti hearts on the crumbling walls
Faded vows in spray paint scrawls
In the cluttered streets
We found our place
Embracing flaws
In a lover's grace

[Chorus]
Beautiful mess
In the chaos we thrive
In chipped paint and neon lights
We come alive
Love in imperfection
A story so old
In our disarray
We found gold

[Verse 3]
Midnight whispers through shattered glass
Lost in the echoes of a broken past
Your wild laugh
My silent cry
In our barbed wire world
We touch the sky

[Bridge]
Among the wreckage
Flowers grow
Bittersweet love
All we know
In the disarray
Hearts beating fast
A beautiful mess
Our love to last

[Chorus]
Beautiful mess
In the chaos we thrive
In chipped paint and neon lights
We come alive
Love in imperfection
A story so old
In our disarray
We found gold

title: Heartbeats in the Dark2 (Remastered)
author: AvaTar ArTs
lyrics:
[Verse]
Soft whispers on the wind
Through the hills we walk
Your hand in mine
Finding strength in the talk
The stars above like old friends lighting the park
Feel my heartbeats in the dark
Heartbeats in the dark

[Verse 2]
Through the shadows we tread
On pathways unknown
But worry not
For you’re not alone
A beacon of hope
In the silence we embark
Feel my heartbeats in the dark
Heartbeats in the dark

[Chorus]
When the night seems long and the road so far
Just listen for the rhythm of my beating heart
Together we’ll journey
Through life’s pitch and bark
Feel my heartbeats in the dark
Heartbeats in the dark

[Verse 3]
In the quiet moments
When words start to fade
And the fears come creeping
Don’t be afraid
For every step you take
I’m never far
Feel my heartbeats in the dark
Heartbeats in the dark

[Bridge]
Close your eyes and lean into the sound
A symphony of love
In the night profound
Unseen but unfaltering
Like an ember’s spark
Feel my heartbeats in the dark
Heartbeats in the dark

[Verse 4]
When the morning comes
And the shadows recede
You’ll see the journey was just what you need
With every heartbeat
A promise to mark
Feel my heartbeats in the dark
Heartbeats in the dark

title: Heroes Rise  - Villains Overthrow
author: AvaTar ArTs
lyrics:

Dark alleys, shadows shifting, echo of gold chains clinking
City breaths tension, heroes and villains, brink the collision

Powerful punches, neon streaks slicing the nightlight

SuperCrooks scheming, villains plotting, dollars dreaming
Capes swishing through smoke, bloody knuckles gleaming

Streets buzz, heroes’ grit, villains’ dark mattering

Heroes rise, villains overthrow
Battles loud, in the grime and glow
Destinies, in the flow, we toe-to-toe

Codename whispers, iron fists crumble
Boom-bap backdrop, heroes leap rooftops
Villains deal crooked plots, ticking bombs, clock stopped

[Verse 4]
Jet-fueled boots, fists igniting cosmic fights
Hero’s loss, villain’s gain, control slipping night
From the ash, reborn the fighters with might
In the chaos, they’re the sparks to the spite

[Bridge]
One leap, two steps, infinity war rolls
Betrayals, truce, fate’s dice in the scrolls
Powers clash, truth masked, reality folds
Heroes rise, villains rule, script unfolds

Beneath the moon’s hostile howl

She hums the blues of a life caught in the traps

Love in a discarded map

Let's get trashy in the moonlight

The stray dogs bark a mournful tune

Free

In the trash we thrive
Hearts wild and debris
